    <h2>What's inside Research #001</h2>
    <p>This is the founding report of Alpha Factory Research. 57 public crypto trading strategies were independently tested through frozen backtesting, forward evidence collection, and cost/concentration analysis.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Liquidation Cascade Continuation:</strong> the strategy that passed all gates — then died on concentration analysis.</li>
      <li><strong>Stop-Hunt Reversal:</strong> 10 paper trades, positive expectancy, one trade from promotion — and why it's still not deployed.</li>
      <li><strong>Cross-Venue Funding Dispersion:</strong> killed in 45 minutes for $0. Why the directional claim was falsified.</li>
      <li><strong>Volatility Compression:</strong> 3 days of live trading, $53 gross profit, -$46 net. The fee trap.</li>
      <li><strong>Pre-Market Convergence:</strong> why the premium widened instead of contracting.</li>
      <li>The complete validation pipeline: Mechanism → DFG → Reality Check → Frozen Backtest → Forward Evidence → Promotion.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>How we test</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:1rem;">
      <div><h3 style="margin-top:0;">Reality Check</h3><p>Frozen, preregistered backtests. No parameter search. Kill at the first broken causal link.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="margin-top:0;">Forward Evidence</h3><p>Prospective paper trading before any capital. We collected 21 forward trades on one strategy alone.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="margin-top:0;">Cost-aware</h3><p>Fees, slippage, funding. Gross profit factor of 1.67 became net 0.59 after costs on our largest test.</p></div>
      <div><h3 style="margin-top:0;">Concentration</h3><p>Two trades contributed 257% of total net profit. We caught it. The strategy was killed.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section id="buy" style="text-align:center;padding:2rem 0;background:#fafafa;border-radius:8px;">
